\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Armor of Arrow Attraction:}{\fs20\cf0  Magical analysis indicates that this armor is a normal suit of }{\i\fs20\cf0 +3 full plate. }{\fs20\cf0 
However, the armor is cursed. It works normally with regard to melee attacks but actually serves to attract ranged weapons. The wearer takes a \endash 15 penalt
y to AC against any attack by a ranged weapon. The true nature of the armor does not reveal itself until the character is fired upon in earnest.
\par Strong abjuration; CL 16th; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, }{\i\fs20\cf0 bestow curse; }{\fs20\cf0 Price 9,000 gp.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Armor of Rage: }{\fs20\cf0 This armor is similar in appearance to }{\i\fs20\cf0 armor of command }{\fs20\cf0 and functions as a suit of }{\i\fs20\cf0 +1 full plate}{\fs20\cf0 
. However, when it is worn, the armor causes the character to take a \endash 4 penalty to Charisma. All unfriendly characters within 300 feet have a +1 morale bonus on attack ro
lls against her. The effect is not noticeable to the wearer or those affected. (In other words, the wearer does not immediately notice that donning the armor is the cause of her problems, nor do foes understand the reason for the depth of their enmity.)

