\par Moderate conjuration; CL 16th; Create Wondrous Item, }{\i\fs20\cf0 mage armor, bestow curse; }{\fs20\cf0 Price 1,200 gp.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Broom of Animated Attack:}{\fs20\cf0  This item is indistinguishable in appearance from a normal broom. It is identical to a }{\i\fs20\cf0 broom of flying }{\fs20\cf0 by all tests short of attempted use.
\par If a command is spoken, the broom does a loop-the-loop with its hopeful rider, dumping him on his head from 1d4+5 feet off the ground (no falling damage, since the fall is less than 10 feet). The broom then attacks the 
victim, swatting the face with the straw or twig end and beating him with the handle end.
\par The broom gets two attacks per round with each end (two swats with the straw and two with the handle, for a total of four attacks per round). It attacks with a +5 bon
us on each attack roll. The straw end causes a victim to be blinded for 1 round when it hits. The handle deals 1d6 points of damage when it hits. The broom has AC 13, 18 hit points, and hardness 4.
\par Moderate transmutation; CL 10th; Create Wondrous Item, }{\i\fs20\cf0 fly, animate objects; }{\fs20\cf0 Price 5,200 gp.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Cloak of Poisonousness:}{\fs20\cf0  This cloak is usually made of a woolen material, although it can be made of leather. A }{\i\fs20\cf0 detect poison }{\fs20\cf0 spell can reveal the presence of poison impregnated in the cloak\rquote 
s fabric. The garment can be handled without harm, but as soon as it is actually donned the wearer is killed instantly unless she succeeds on a DC 28 Fortitude save.
\par Once donned, a }{\i\fs20\cf0 cloak of poisonousness }{\fs20\cf0 can be removed only with a }{\i\fs20\cf0 remove curse }{\fs20\cf0 spell; doing this destroys the magical property of the cloak. If a }{\i\fs20\cf0 neutralize poison }{\fs20\cf0 
spell is then used, it is possible to revive the victim with a }{\i\fs20\cf0 raise dead }{\fs20\cf0 or }{\i\fs20\cf0 resurrection }{\fs20\cf0 spell, but not before.
