must be coated in blood every day, or its bonus fades away (until the mace is coated again). The character using this mace must make a DC 13 Will save every day it is within his possession or become chaotic evil.
\par Moderate abjuration; CL 8th; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, creator must be at least 9th level and chaotic evil; Price 16,000 gp.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Medallion of Thought Projection:}{\fs20\cf0  This device seems like a }{\i\fs20\cf0 medallion of thoughts}{\fs20\cf0 
, even down to the range at which it functions, except that the thoughts overheard are muffled and distorted, requiring a DC 15 Will save to sort out. However, while the user thinks she is picking up the thoughts of others, all she is really hearing are f
igments created by the medallion itself. These illusory thoughts always seem plausible and thus can seriously mislead any who rely upon them. What\rquote 
s worse, unknown to her, the cursed medallion actually broadcasts her thoughts to creatures in the path of the beam, thus alerting them to her presence.
\par Faint divination; CL 7th; Create Wondrous Item, }{\i\fs20\cf0 detect thoughts, ghost sound; }{\fs20\cf0 Price 1,800 gp.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Necklace of Strangulation:}{\fs20\cf0  A }{\i\fs20\cf0 necklace of strangulation }{\fs20\cf0 appears to be a rare and wondrous piece of valuable jewelry and, short of the use of something as powerful as a }{\i\fs20\cf0 miracle }{\fs20\cf0 
